HEADWORD: Cretinism
<hw>Cre"tin*ism</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧"t⟦icr⟧n*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>cr⟦eacute⟧tinisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>A condition of
endemic or inherited idiocy, accompanied by physical degeneracy and
deformity (usually with goiter), frequent in certain mountain valleys,
esp. of the Alps.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cretinous</ent>⟦br⟧
